description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 2 Medical Laboratory Assistant&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A modernised clinical pathology service, proud to deliver excellence for clients, patients and staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;North West London Pathology (NWLP) is a new partnership between Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust, Chelsea &amp; Westminster NHS Trust and The Hillingdon Hospitals NHS Trust. We deliver our services at six hospital sites across North West London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are now offering a fantastic opportunity to join our friendly and dedicated Microbiology team at Charing Cross Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 2&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The main duties include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;receipt of samples via pneumatic tube, porters, couriers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;specimen triage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;specimen data entry onto LIMS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;sample labelling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specifics: skills/experience required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 2&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have an interest in laboratory work and be committed to being part of a team that delivers a quality service to patients. You must be organised and methodical with high attention to detail and be prepared to handle biological materials (patient samples). You must have good keyboard skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For this role, you will participate in a shift system (early /late shift)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Staff are expected to work across our six hospital sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to your development and you will have opportunities to fulfil your potential with NWLP.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to hearing from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sweenie Goonesekera on 020 331 17883&lt;/p&gt;
